                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Centre page, in ink by a modern hand: <quote>Psalterium cum Canticis Ferialibus et Festivis per manus Johannis de nova Plzna 1472</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page, in ink by an early modern hand: <quote>Psalterium Dauidis Regis</quote>. Bottom of page, in ink by a late medieval or early modern hand: <quote>per quiquagenos dauid canit ordine psalmos <gap reason="damage"/> sub bis mille sexcentos canit ille</quote>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="2r" to="86v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Psalm numbers in ink in the margin by a late medieval or early modern hand. The majority follow the Vulgate numbering; however, between Psalm 9:20(10) and 16(17) the numbering follows the Hebrew version (<locus from="5v" to="8r" scheme="folios"/>). Psalm 17(18) is not numbered (<locus from="8v" to="8v" scheme="folios"/>) and psalm 18(19) is numbered as 18, in accordance with the Vulgate numbering (<locus from="10v" to="10v" scheme="folios"/>). Ps. 67:20 is numbered as <quote>68</quote> and Ps. 68 as <quote>69</quote> and Ps 68:20 as <quote>70</quote> (<locus from="38r" to="40v" scheme="folios"/>). At Ps. 69 the erroneous number <quote>lxxi</quote> is crossed out (<locus from="40v" to="40v" scheme="folios"/>), and Ps. 70 is not numbered. Psalm 104 is incorrectly numbered as <quote>103</quote> (<locus from="63r" to="63r" scheme="folios"/>). Below some of these psalm numbers, a modern hand has corrected (or added) the Vulgate number in pencil.
                                        <!--(5v, 10v, 87r).--></note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="3r" to="3r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Top of page, in ink by an early modern hand: a note in Czech.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="3v" to="84r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>In the margin, at the penitential psalms, in ink by a contemporary hand: the ordinal number of the psalm in Czech (last two in Roman numerals).</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locusGrp>
                                        <locus from="25r" to="25r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="68r" to="68r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    </locusGrp>
                                    <note>Right margin, in ink by an early modern hand (same as <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="3r" to="3r" scheme="folios"/>): a note in Czech.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="87v" to="101r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Marginal references to the biblical passages in red by a contemporary hand. Above these, a modern hand has occasionally added the biblical book in pencil.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink; rubrics in red (possibly in more than one hand (c.f. e.g. <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="52v" to="52v" scheme="folios"/>). Enlarged and decorated initials at Ps. 1, 20, 32, 45, 59, 73, 89, 101, and 109, and two of the canticles. First line in display script touched in red at every enlarged and decorated psalm initial except Ps. 32, 89, and the canticle on <locus from="101r" to="101r" scheme="folios"/>; display script also at <locus from="39r" to="39r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 68), <locus from="40v" to="40v" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 70), <locus from="100r" to="100r" scheme="folios"/> (canticle), and of a different style at <locus from="38r" to="38r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 67:20). The display script exhibits a mix of Roman and Greek letters (e.g. <locus from="34r" to="34r" scheme="folios"/>).</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 1), <locus from="11r" to="11r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 20), <locus from="17v" to="17v" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 32), <locus from="27r" to="27r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 45), <locus from="30v" to="30v" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 51), <locus from="34r" to="34r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 59), <locus from="43r" to="43r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 73), <locus from="55r" to="55r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 89), <locus from="60v" to="60v" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 101), <locus from="71v" to="71v" scheme="folios"/>, (Ps. 118; the red half only), and <locus from="91r" to="91r" scheme="folios"/> (divisio psalmi), <locus from="95v" to="95v" scheme="folios"/> (canticle), <locus from="101r" to="101r" scheme="folios"/> (canticle): puzzle initial over 3-6 lines in red and brown, some with penwork or flourishing.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="102v" scheme="folios"/>: plain psalm initials over 2 lines in red.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="102v" scheme="folios"/>: plain initials over 1 line in red.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="68r" to="68r" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 109): plain psalm initial over 3 lines with interior reserved shapes.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="94v" to="94v" scheme="folios"/>: plain canticle initial <quote>T</quote> over 2 lines in red on a green background possibly added later.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="21v" to="101v" scheme="folios"/>: initials (and some ascenders) on top line elongated and embellished with flourising in brown.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="74r" to="85v" scheme="folios"/> (quire 8): psalm initials touched in yellow; rubrics underlined in yellow.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="49v" to="49v" scheme="folios"/> (Ps. 79): initial missing.</p>
                                    <p> Guide letters visible.</p>
                                </decoNote>
